(a) $x=r \sin \mathrm{~A} \cos \mathrm{C}, y=r \sin \mathrm{~A} \sin \mathrm{C}, z=r \cos \mathrm{~A}$

$$
x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2}=r^{2} \sin ^{2} \mathrm{~A} \cos ^{2} \mathrm{C}+r^{2} \sin ^{2} \mathrm{~A} \sin ^{2} \mathrm{C}+r^{2} \cos ^{2} \mathrm{~A}
$$

$$
\begin{aligned}
& =\left(r^{2} \sin ^{2} A\right)\left(\cos ^{2} C+\sin ^{2} C\right)+r^{2} \cos ^{2} A \\
& =r^{2} \sin ^{2} A(1)+r^{2} \cos ^{2} A \\
& =r^{2}\left(\sin ^{2} A+\cos ^{2} A\right)=r^{2}
\end{aligned}
$$

