(d) We have,
$\sin (A+B)=\sin A \cos B+\cos A \sin B$
Putting $A=45^{\circ}, B=30^{\circ}$

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \therefore \sin \left(45^{\circ}+30^{\circ}\right)=\sin 45^{\circ} \cos 30^{\circ}+\cos 30^{\circ} \sin 45^{\circ} \\
& \therefore \sin 75^{\circ}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \times \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}+\frac{1}{2} \times \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}=\frac{\sqrt{3}+1}{2 \sqrt{2}}
\end{aligned}
$$

